---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`Tiered Usage Pricing (Tiers, Overages, Minimums) | ${siteName}`}
  description="How to design tiered usage pricing that reduces bill shock while protecting margins at p90 usage."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Tiered usage pricing</h1>
    <p>Tiered pricing combines predictable minimums with volume discounts so heavy customers pay fairly without surprising bills.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>Start with a minimum</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Use a platform fee to cover baseline support and overhead.</li>
        <li>Include a small amount of usage to reduce bill shock for new customers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Choose tier breakpoints</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Pick thresholds around meaningful usage levels (p50, p75, p90).</li>
        <li>Model costs at p90 so your gross margin holds for heavy customers.</li>
        <li>Keep the number of tiers small (2–4) for buyer clarity.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Reduce bill shock</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Publish example bills at “typical” and “heavy” usage.</li>
        <li>Provide usage alerts or soft caps when spikes happen.</li>
        <li>Prefer clear units over abstract credits.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/tiered-usage-pricing-calculator/">Tiered usage pricing calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/usage-based-pricing-calculator/">Usage-based pricing calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/usage-based-pricing-examples/">Usage pricing examples</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/usage-based-pricing/">Glossary: usage-based pricing</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/saas-gross-margin-targets/">Gross margin targets</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

